# No allow(dead_code)

**Do not use `#[allow(dead_code)]` (or `#[allow(dead_code)]` on fields/items) in this project.**

If the compiler reports dead code:

- **Use the value** somewhere (e.g. in metrics, logs, or logic), or
- **Remove the code** if it is truly unused, or
- **Rename** to indicate intentionally unused (e.g. `_total`) only when the value is required by an API/schema and cannot be removed.

Do not suppress the warning with `#[allow(dead_code)]`. This rule exists so we fix or remove dead code instead of hiding it.
